iti paryukṣaṇamaṃtra ||056:044||
prajāpataye svāhā |
indrāya svāhā |
agnaye svāhā |
somāya svāhā |
antarikṣāya svāhā |
oṃ bhū svāhā |
oṃ bhuvaḥ svāhā |
oṃ sbaḥ svāhāḥ |
iti mūlahomāhutayaḥ ||056:045||
evaṃ vediko'gniḥ saṃṣṭuto bhavati |
athātaḥ paristaraṇa devatāḥ kathyante ||056:046||
parisamūhane kāśyapaḥ |
upalepane viśvavedevāḥ |
ullekhane mitrā varuṇau |
ullikhane pṛthvī |
ampukṣaṇe gaṃdharvā |
agniḥ sādane śarvaḥ ||056:047||
manuruvāca |

parisamūhyopalikhyollikhana karmavidhirucyate |
dakṣiṇāsādane brahmā |
uttarataḥ pūraṇe sāgarāḥ |
āstaraṇe trasāḥ |
athāvasādane śatakratuḥ |
pavitravandhane pitaraḥ |
prokṣaṇī saṃskāre mātaraḥ ||056:048||
juhvate śruve śruvāpāśca brahmaviṣṇumaheśvarāḥ |
ājyātapane vasavaḥ |
adhīśravaṇe vaivasvataḥ |
paryagnikaraṇe marutaḥ |
udvāsane skandaḥ |
utpanna pratyutpavane candraḥ dyauḥ ||056:049||
ājyāvekṣaṇe diśaḥ sarvāḥ |
pavitradhāraṇe praṇītāḥ |
yāmumā devī |
īdhme ca lakṣmīḥ |
viśvasya viśvābhūtāni ||056:050||
pūrvoktānāntu vahṇīnāmekamānīya pāvakam |
homakarma prakarttavyaṃ vidhiṃ jñātvā mahāmune ||056:051||
etā vai devatāḥ proktā brāhmaṇānāṃ hitāya vai |
yajñeṣu paśubaṃdheṣu sarvayajña kriyāsu ca ||056:052||
iti śrī devīpurāṇebhyudayapāde havanavidhirnāṃma ṣaṭpaṃcāśo'dhyāyaḥ |

